OL,3,CParents fines for school absence 'need
OL,4,Cto be consigned to past'
OL,6,FThreatening parents with "punitive"
OL,7,Ffines when their child misses school
OL,8,Fis not reducing absences and should
OL,9,Finstead be "consigned to the past",
OL,10,Fthe former Children's Commissioner for
OL,11,FEngland has said.
OL,13,FInstead developing a "more inclusive"
OL,14,Fschool environment could help tackle
OL,15,Fthe attendance crisis rather than a
OL,16,F"one-size-fits-all" approach, Anne
OL,17,FLongfield said.
